## Changes Made

### 1. `docs/specs/super-ralph-spec.md` — Three new subsections after §2.4.5

- **§2.4.5.1 Infrastructure Scope** — Explicitly states interactive mode MUST NOT use: event system, run tracker, progress log, transcripts, or console renderer. Each exclusion references the relevant spec section.

- **§2.4.5.2 Cleanup Guarantees** — Defines that interactive mode MUST clean up on ALL exit paths: abort the session (best-effort) and close the server. References §2.8 as the engine equivalent.

- **§2.4.5.3 Return Value and Exit Behavior** — Specifies `InteractiveResult` as the return type (with full schema), defines CLI exit codes (0 for complete, 1 for blocked/error), and states `--json` is silently ignored.

### 2. `docs/specs/super-ralph-spec.md` — §11.2 expanded

Added a paragraph explaining why the new subsections exist: an implementer can't safely infer exclusions from "MUST NOT use the engine" alone.

### 3. `spec/modules/integrations/interactive.md` — New "Infrastructure Scope" section

Added a concise summary section cross-referencing all the new spec subsections, so the module-level spec stays in sync with the main spec.

